However, one of the criteria mentioned in the list states that the Russian anti-doping authorities must publicly accept the reported results of the WADA approved investigation by Canadian lawyer Richard McLaren on alleged state-sponsored doping in Russian sport.
As regards the matter, Mutko said: 'We are carrying out the investigation because our anti-doping system has acknowledged a mistake.
All the measures have been implemented.
But there were no public programmes and we will not admit something that does not exist. '
His words were in line with those of Vitaly Smirnov, head of the independent Russian Anti-Doping Commission.
