No one intends to accept this report unconditionally, "added Smirnov.
In November 2015, in the wake of the doping scandal, RUNADA was excluded from conducting doping checks in Russia.
However, it was allowed to plan and coordinate tests under the supervision of international experts and the UK Anti-Doping (UKAD).
After a visit to the organization ’ s headquarters in Moscow in July, WADA-Director General Olivier Niggli stated that RUSADA is "moving in the right direction" to be reinstated.
