Helicopter units flew an additional 11 hours on that day for “non-presidential support missions. ”
The White House said that taxpayers did not take the burden on any of the other props presented at the event.
A spokesman for Sikorsky said that the company was not involved in displaying the helicopter on South Lawn.
HMMX-1 does not maintain budget records for presidential flights, and it is difficult to determine the exact cost of the event.
However, according to hourly rates from the US Department of Defense for the 2017 fiscal year, the DoD refund for VH-3D is $24,380 per flight hour.
Records of the unit record the flight time of the aircraft as 30 minutes from the base of the Marine Corps Air Facility in Quantico in Virginia.
The White House argues that the actual cost of operating the helicopter is well below this rate.
'Setting taxpayers' costs on the basis of estimates of the reimbursement rates is highly misleading, 'said Walters.
'These estimates include personnel, maintenance and many other hidden costs included in the annual funds'.
According to a 2015 RAND study, the refund rates for DoD do not include personnel costs, but take into account the costs of fuel, maintenance, and contract conclusion.
At that time, the former White House press spokesman, Sean Spicer, defended the helicopter ’ s use for the event.
