Interview: 'Domspatzen report discharges the papacy brother Georg Ratzinger'
The Regensburg Cathedral Spatzen report on the cases of abuse relieves the burden of the Papst brother Georg Ratzinger.
This is what the author and historian Michael Hesemann means.
The final report on the abuse scandal in the Regensburg Cathedral Spatzen continues to give rise to discussion.
Christian Weisnder, spokesman of the reform movement "We are Church", declared after publication to the German Press Agency that he expects an apology from the former bishop of Regensburg and today Cardinal Gerhard Ludwig Müller as well as from the cathedral master Georg Ratzinger, the 93-year-old brother of the celebrated Pope Benedict XVI.
