The Vatican newspaper, "Osservatore Romano", on the other hand, criticized the use of 'double standards' in reporting on violence in the Cathedral jokes.
With regard to the attacks in Regensburg, no one doubts that these are "shameful and shameful acts" that should be punished and prevented in the future; but what is striking is the "degree of media manipulation", according to the author Lucetta Scarafbia, historian and member of the Italian National Bioethics Committee.
